---
name: scljet-sql-having
description: SclJet SQL HAVING — filter GROUP BY groups by an aggregate or column condition (matches reference sqlite3)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL HAVING

`… GROUP BY col HAVING (agg|col) op literal` keeps only the groups whose aggregate (or group
column) satisfies the condition, after aggregation. Every result is byte-identical to reference
sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def run(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER, dept TEXT, age INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("eng"), SqlInteger(30L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("sales"), SqlInteger(40L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("eng"), SqlInteger(25L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("hr"), SqlInteger(50L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("sales"), SqlInteger(35L)),
       List(SqlInteger(6L), SqlText("eng"), SqlInteger(45L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    run(db, "SELECT dept, COUNT(*) FROM t GROUP BY dept HAVING COUNT(*) > 1")
    run(db, "SELECT dept, SUM(age) FROM t GROUP BY dept HAVING SUM(age) >= 75")
    run(db, "SELECT dept, COUNT(*) FROM t GROUP BY dept HAVING dept = 'eng'")
    run(db, "SELECT dept, MAX(age) FROM t GROUP BY dept HAVING MAX(age) < 50")
    run(db, "SELECT dept, MIN(age) FROM t WHERE age > 26 GROUP BY dept HAVING COUNT(*) >= 2")
```
